#: ../../../cmds/funcsave.rst:2
msgid ""
"funcsave - save the definition of a function to the user's autoload directory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funcsave.rst:5
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funcsave.rst:7
msgid ""
"funcsave FUNCTION_NAME\n"
"funcsave [-q | --quiet] [(-d | --directory) DIR] FUNCTION_NAME"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funcsave.rst:14
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funcsave.rst:16
msgid ""
"``funcsave`` saves a function to a file in the fish configuration directory. "
"This function will be :ref:`automatically loaded <syntax-function-"
"autoloading>` by current and future fish sessions. This can be useful to "
"commit functions created interactively for permanent use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funcsave.rst:18
msgid ""
"If you have erased a function using :doc:`functions <functions>`'s ``--"
"erase`` option, ``funcsave`` will remove the saved function definition."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funcsave.rst:20
msgid ""
"Because fish loads functions on-demand, saved functions cannot serve as :ref:"
"`event handlers <event>` until they are run or otherwise sourced. To "
"activate an event handler for every new shell, add the function to the :ref:"
"`configuration file <configuration>` instead of using ``funcsave``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funcsave.rst:22
msgid ""
"This is often used after :doc:`funced <funced>`, which opens the function in "
"``$EDITOR`` or ``$VISUAL`` and loads it into the current session afterwards."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funcsave.rst:24
msgid ""
"To view a function's current definition, use :doc:`functions <functions>` "
"or :doc:`type <type>`."
msgstr ""
